Ozone




General information

Ozone is molocules that absorbs 99% of harmful UV rays.


Good Ozone

Good Ozone exists in the stratosphere. It forms when solar radiation splits O2 molocules. It benefits humans because it protects us from 99% of harmful UV rays. Ozone depletion is the thinning of the ozone layer. The effects of it are less protection from the sun. Humans can reduce ozone depletion by reducing their carbon emissions.


Bad Ozone

Bad ozone exists in the troposphere. It forms by NOx (Nitrous oxides) and VOCs (volatile organic compounds). Humans contrbute to this by fossil fuel usage, industry, and power plants. Humans can reduce their impact by using less fossil fuels.
